history.text: Did you ever watch Toy Story?
I have seen all three.  I never realized that Joss Whedon had a hand in the movie.
Were you on Team Woody or Team Buzz when they were competing for Andy's affection?
I'm not familiar with Whedon, I only watched the first one.
Buzz!
You?
Woody was quite a jerk in the first movie.
Yeah, I thought so too.
It really did break barriers for Disney entering the computer generated animation field.
Plus I thought Buzz was kinda clumsy and more likeable
For sure!
I think that's the main reason it was such a hit.
How were the other 2? I never watched them
I think 3 is my favorite of the set.  It had a lot of emotional moments and call backs to the first movies.
I might need to watch it. So I can catch up.
I really liked the green army men in the scene this paragraph is describing.  It made me look at them a new way.
I remember the only reason I went to see the first one was because my daughter was of the age at the time and I was looking for a kid appropriate movie
True. They were kinda funny.
I thought TIm Allen was the right match for the voice over of Buzz
I still have trouble throwing away my kids toys because of the way the toys were given personalities and responded to being discarded.
The voice actors were all amazing.
I used to have an extensive collection of Army Men.
My mom threw them all away. :(
I guess to your point they were all screaming when they hit the trash can
The CLAW!!!  I love the aliens and the crane game scene.
Yes. Those machines are impossible to operate.
I love looking for the Pizza Planet truck in all the Pixar films.
I kinda found Potato Head to be likeable.
likable
Oh and Rex!
I have an obsession with the claw games and this movie probably helped add to that.
Ha! I don't even know where I would find one anymore.
You gotta figure that a dog would be a toys worst nightmare.
Did't the dog eat some of the green army men?
I can't remember
I don't think we ever get to see the dog actually interact with the toys in the first movie.
Oh, okay. I really need to check out the other 2 movies.
I guess if the movie were made today, Woody and Buzz would have been riding a drone instead of rc car.
But now that you told me, I'll probably skip the second one.
Yeah good point!!
Or one of those 2 wheeled scooters
The second wasn't bad but is definitely the weakest of the 3.
I can't remember what they are called.
Oh yeah!   I could see them trying to operate a hoverboard.
How did you stick out with even watching the third one, if the second one was not that good?
I would've quit then.
By the time the third came along, I had kids of my own and took the oldest to see it with a church group.
SegWay. That's it
Makes sense.
I am glad that Buzz and Woody ended up being friends.
Was that in the third movie?
Well, even at the end of the first they were working together and had come to an understanding.
Or event he first one. I can't remember, it was a while ago
Right!
Funny because to this day if I were to imagine toys that had a voice it would sound like Tim Allen.
I could see that.  All Mr. Potato Heads sound like the toy story one in my head as well.
The voice of Potato was the guy from that sitcom Cheers, right?
I think so and Mrs. Potato Head later was the voice of George's mom from Seinfield.
Oh, I never really watched Seinfield, but sounds like I missed out.
This kind of makes me want to go watch the movie again.
Ha. I was actually surprised Rotten Tomatoes gave it that high of a rating. Aren't they  generally pretty brutal with their ratings?

uid1response.feedback: Other User left conversation after a while we were chatting, so I ended it.

uid2response.feedback: This was a fun conversation about Toy Story.
